Future<void> insertSampleData() async {
  final result = await db.query('orders');

  if (result.isEmpty) {
    await db.insert('orders', {
      'product_name': 'Laptop',
      'quantity': 2,
    });

    await db.insert('orders', {
      'product_name': 'Phone',
      'quantity': 5,
    });

    await db.insert('orders', {
      'product_name': 'Keyboard',
      'quantity': 3,
    });
  }
}

3. A 3–4 line note explaining what you changed and why the AI's version needed it.

During testing, I found that the AI-generated code inserted sample records every time the app started, creating duplicate data in the database.
I modified the insert function to first check whether the table is empty before adding sample records.
This ensures that the sample data is added only on the first app launch and improves database handling.
